$ Browser Object Model: The document object

The `document` object is the root element of the → development/web/DOM[document object model].

Interestingly, there is a `document.body` property but no `document.html` or `document.head` property.
-
However, the document element (that is → development/web/HTML/tags/html[`<html>`]) can be accessed via `document.documentElement`.
(It is unclear to me if the terminology is correct to name `document` the root object, because I believed for a long time that `<html>` is the root element).

{ document.compatMode #document-compatMode

  The the value of the property `document.compatMode` is dependent on the → development/web/browser/layout-engine#browser-rendering-mode[rendering mode] of a
  → development/web/browser/layout-engine[web browser's layout endinge]. It is set to one of the following two values:
    • `BackCompat` (quirks mode)
    • `CSS1Compat` (standard mode)

}
